HEADWORD: lincomycin
<hw>lincomycin</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>An antibacterial antibiotic
obtained from the bacterium <spn>Streptomyces lincolnensis</spn> and
used in the treatment of certain penicillin-resistant
infections.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

